- Django is an high-level python framework that enables rapid development of secure and maintainable websites
- Django follows MVT - Model View Template
- Django has builtin features
  - Authentication
  - Database Management (Django ORM)
  - Admin Interface
  - Security features

  Step 1: Create a virtual env
    python -m venv venv
    venv\Scripts\activate #windows
    source venv/bin/activate #mac/linux

  Step 2: Install Django
    pip install django

  Step 3: Application Requirements
  - HMS - Hospital Management System
  - Appointments, users, bills
  
  Step 4: Create Django Project
    django-admin startproject medhahms .
    python3 manage.py runserver

  Note: Have your Sqlite3 extension installed in vscode
  so that you can see the db tables in vscode directly

  Step 5: Make django migrations
    python3 manage.py migrate

  After this you'll see db tables created for default apps

  Step 6: Understand Django Project
    - settings.py
    -- Register apps
    -- Database
    -- Middleware
    -- Security

  Step 6: Create & Register App - patients
  python3 manage.py startapp patients
  Register app inside project's settings.py

  Step 6.1 Create Model
  from django.db import models

  # Create your models here.
  class Patient(models.Model):
      name = models.CharField(max_length=200)
      phone = models.CharField(max_length=15)
      email = models.EmailField()

  Step 6.2 - Apply migrations
    python3 manage.py makemigrations
    python3 manage.py migrate

  step 6.3 - Admin setup for patient
    inside patients/admin.py

    from django.contrib import admin
    from .models import Patient
    
    # Register your models here.
    admin.site.register(Patient)

  step 6.4 create admin superuser
    python3 manage.py createsuperuser
    #fill username, password, email

  step 6.5 start server and goto /admin & login











    


    
    
